hy, understanding what to look for in a project can help you make the right decision. \r\n\r\nIf you have decided to take the leap into real estate investment, here are a few tips to follow.'),(381,48,'_accordion-chapters_0_content','field_5afac5c5447e1'),(382,48,'accordion-chapters','1'),(383,48,'_accordion-chapters','field_5afac592447df'),(384,9,'accordion-chapters_0_chapter-number','CHAPTER 1'),(385,9,'_accordion-chapters_0_chapter-number','field_5afac74e5acb2'),(386,9,'accordion-chapters_0_chapter-title','Things First-Time Home Buyers Should Know Before Investing '),(387,9,'_accordion-chapters_0_chapter-title','field_5afac75b5acb3'),(388,49,'main-content','Being able to own a home of their own is often the biggest motivation for people to work hard and save money. In India, a home is more than just a piece of property, it is also a source of pride, security and stability. More Indians today are looking to invest in residential property, instead of living in rented houses as tenants.\r\n\r\n<span class=\"regular-pro-semibold\">The Economic Survey 2017-18 revealed that only 28% of urban Indians live in rented houses as compared to 1961 when as many as 54% lived in rented houses.</span>\r\n\r\nThe current Indian real estate market is booming, making it the perfect investment opportunity for almost guaranteed returns. Rapid improvements in infrastructural developments in the suburbs and increased competitiveness among property developers have given home buyers immense choice when it comes to finding a home to invest in. \r\n\r\nThese market conditions have also been supported by a slew of economic policies introduced by the government to make home ownership accessible to all. The RERA act was a landmark move to bring about transparency in the real estate sector and protect a buyers interests. The complex and highly variable tax structure in real estate was also eliminated with the introduction of GST, which standardised tax rates across the country. But, arguably, the most ambitious move to encourage more people to buy homes was the launch of the Housing for All scheme which offered heavily subsidised interest rates on home loans. This was one of the best first-time home buyer benefits to encourage more people to invest. \r\n\r\nThese factors have made this the perfect time to invest in a home of your own. However, for first-time home buyers, the entire process can seem confusing and intimidating. This in-depth home buyers guide will help you understand every step involved in the homebuying process and ensure that it goes smoothly.\r\n'),(389,49,'_main-content','field_5afa9f11ebf40'),(390,49,'chapters_0_image','35'),(391,49,'_chapters_0_image','field_5afaa63b36c3d'),(392,49,'chapters_0_title','Chapter 1'),(393,49,'_chapters_0_title','field_5afaa64536c3e'),(394,49,'chapters_0_content','Things First-Time Home Buyers Should Know Before Investing'),(395,49,'_chapters_0_content','field_5afaa64c36c3f'),(396,49,'chapters_1_image','36'),(397,49,'_chapters_1_image','field_5afaa63b36c3d'),(398,49,'chapters_1_title','Chapter 2'),(399,49,'_chapters_1_title','field_5afaa64536c3e'),(400,49,'chapters_1_content','Best Investment  Destinations to Buy a Home'),(401,49,'_chapters_1_content','field_5afaa64c36c3f'),(402,49,'chapters_2_image','37'),(403,49,'_chapters_2_image','field_5afaa63b36c3d'),(404,49,'chapters_2_title','Chapter 3'),(405,49,'_chapters_2_title','field_5afaa64536c3e'),(406,49,'chapters_2_content','Types of Residential  Property'),(407,49,'_chapters_2_content','field_5afaa64c36c3f'),(408,49,'chapters_3_image','30'),(409,49,'_chapters_3_image','field_5afaa63b36c3d'),(410,49,'chapters_3_title','Chapter 4'),(411,49,'_chapters_3_title','field_5afaa64536c3e'),(412,49,'chapters_3_content','Things to Check Before Booking a Home'),(413,49,'_chapters_3_content','field_5afaa64c36c3f'),(414,49,'chapters_4_image','31'),(415,49,'_chapters_4_image','field_5afaa63b36c3d'),(416,49,'chapters_4_title','Chapter 5'),(417,49,'_chapters_4_title','field_5afaa64536c3e'),(418,49,'chapters_4_content','Documents Required to  Buy a House'),(419,49,'_chapters_4_content','field_5afaa64c36c3f'),(420,49,'chapters_5_image','32'),(421,49,'_chapters_5_image','field_5afaa63b36c3d'),(422,49,'chapters_5_title','Chapter 6'),(423,49,'_chapters_5_title','field_5afaa64536c3e'),(424,49,'chapters_5_content','The Complete Home Loan Application Process'),(425,49,'_chapters_5_content','field_5afaa64c36c3f'),(426,49,'chapters_6_image','33'),(427,49,'_chapters_6_image','field_5afaa63b36c3d'),(428,49,'chapters_6_title','Chapter 7'),(429,49,'_chapters_6_title','field_5afaa64536c3e'),(430,49,'chapters_6_content','How to Save Taxes on a  Real Estate Investment'),(431,49,'_chapters_6_content','field_5afaa64c36c3f'),(432,49,'chapters_7_image','34'),(433,49,'_chapters_7_image','field_5afaa63b36c3d'),(434,49,'chapters_7_title','Chapter 8'),(435,49,'_chapters_7_title','field_5afaa64536c3e'),(436,49,'chapters_7_content','A Step-by-Step Guide on How to Register Your Property '),(437,49,'_chapters_7_content','field_5afaa64c36c3f'),(438,49,'chapters','8'),(439,49,'_chapters','field_5afaa63036c3c'),(440,49,'chapter1','41'),(441,49,'_chapter1','field_5afabe9f63ba8'),(442,49,'accordion-chapters_0_image','41'),(443,49,'_accordion-chapters_0_image','field_5afac5ad447e0'),(444,49,'accordion-chapters_0_content','You might have decided to invest in real estate, but how do you find the right home to purchase? A glossy brochure can seem very attractive, but there are deeper aspects to look into before deciding whether a property will be a worthwhile investment. \r\n\r\nKnowing exactly what questions to ask before zeroing in on a property can be the difference between a good investment and a bad investment. \r\n\r\nA smart real estate purchase will deliver a high ROI margin while a bad real estate investment depreciates over time. For most ongoing projects, the factors that can influence price appreciation might not be immediately evident. This is why, understanding what to look for in a project can help you make the right decision. \r\n\r\nIf you have decided to take the leap into real estate investment, here are a few tips to follow.'),(445,49,'_accordion-chapters_0_content','field_5afac5c5447e1'),(446,49,'accordion-chapters','1'),(447,49,'_accordion-chapters','field_5afac592447df'),(448,49,'accordion-chapters_0_chapter-number','CHAPTER 1'),(449,49,'_accordion-chapters_0_chapter-number','field_5afac74e5acb2'),(450,49,'accordion-chapters_0_chapter-title','Things First-Time Home Buyers Should Know Before Investing'),(451,49,'_accordion-chapters_0_chapter-title','field_5afac75b5acb3'),(452,50,'_wp_attached_file','2018/05/chapter1-sub-image.jpg'),(453,50,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:1365;s:6:\"height\";i:350;s:4:\"file\";s:30:\"2018/05/chapter1-sub-image.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:4:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:30:\"chapter1-sub-image-150x150.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:6:\"medium\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:29:\"chapter1-sub-image-300x77.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:300;s:6:\"height\";i:77;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:12:\"medium_large\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:30:\"chapter1-sub-image-768x197.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:768;s:6:\"height\";i:197;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:5:\"large\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:31:\"chapter1-sub-image-1024x263.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:1024;s:6:\"height\";i:263;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:12:{s:8:\"aperture\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";s:1:\"0\";s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:1:\"0\";s:3:\"iso\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";s:1:\"0\";s:8:\"keywords\";a:0:{}}}'),(454,51,'main-content','Being able to own a home of their own is often the biggest motivation for people to work hard and save money. In India, a home is more than just a piece of property, it is also a source of pride, security and stability. More Indians today are looking to invest in residential property, instead of living in rented houses as tenants.\r\n\r\n<span class=\"regular-pro-semibold\">The Economic Survey 2017-18 revealed that only 28% of urban Indians live in rented houses as compared to 1961 when as many as 54% lived in rented houses.</span>\r\n\r\nThe current Indian real estate market is booming, making it the perfect investment opportunity for almost guaranteed returns. Rapid improvements in infrastructural developments in the suburbs and increased competitiveness among property developers have given home buyers immense choice when it comes to finding a home to invest in. \r\n\r\nThese market conditions have also been supported by a slew of economic policies introduced by the government to make home ownership accessible to all. The RERA act was a landmark move to bring about transparency in the real estate sector and protect a buyers interests. The complex and highly variable tax structure in real estate was also eliminated with the introduction of GST, which standardised tax rates across the country. But, arguably, the most ambitious move to encourage more people to buy homes was the launch of the Housing for All scheme which offered heavily subsidised interest rates on home loans. This was one of the best first-time home buyer benefits to encourage more people to invest. \r\n\r\nThese factors have made this the perfect time to invest in a home of your own. However, for first-time home buyers, the entire process can seem confusing and intimidating. This in-depth home buyers guide will help you understand every step involved in the homebuying process and ensure that it goes smoothly.\r\n'),(455,51,'_main-content','field_5afa9f11ebf40'),(456,51,'chapters_0_image','35'),(457,51,'_chapters_0_image','field_5afaa63b36c3d'),(458,51,'chapters_0_title','Chapter 1'),(459,51,'_chapters_0_title','field_5afaa64536c3e'),(460,51